
Peja Lindholm
instance
Peter \"Peja\" Rutger Lindholm (born 2 June 1970 in Ã–stersund, Sweden) is a retired Swedish curler. Lindholm is currently the national coach of the Swedish Curling Association. Over his two-decade curling playing career, Lindholm won three world championships as a skip, winning in 1997, 2001 and 2004. He is also a two-time European champion (1998, and 2001) and a is former world junior champion (1989). Lindholm announced his retirement from curling following the 2007 European Curling Championships.
